(44, 4, 22, 44, 9, 33, 33, NULL, 'Healing of the Sick', 'Both passages emphasize miraculous healings of individuals suffering from ailments. The first passage mentions a man healed after being over forty years old, while the second describes Eneas, who had been sick for eight years.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 22, 40, 9, 20, 20, NULL, 'Healing and Age Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of healing in both passages. The man in Acts is noted for his age, while the woman in Matthew has suffered for twelve years, emphasizing the significance of their conditions in relation to miraculous healing.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 22, 42, 13, 11, 11, NULL, 'Healing of the Infirmed', 'Both passages emphasize the miraculous healing of individuals suffering from physical ailments. The man in Acts was healed after being infirm for over forty years, while the woman in Luke suffered from her condition for eighteen years, highlighting the transformative power of healing.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 22, 43, 9, 1, 1, NULL, 'Healing of the Disabled', 'Both passages emphasize miraculous healings involving individuals with significant disabilities. The man in Acts was healed after being disabled for over forty years, while the man in John was blind from birth, showcasing the transformative power of Jesus'' miracles.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 22, 44, 3, 2, 2, 'the man was above forty years old', 'Healing of the Lame Man', 'Both passages emphasize the healing of a man who was lame from birth. The SOURCE verse notes that the man was over forty years old, highlighting the significance of the miracle in Acts 3:2.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 23, 47, 6, 14, 17, 'their own company', 'Separation from Unbelievers', 'This connection highlights the theme of community and separation from unbelievers. In Acts 4:23, the apostles return to their own company after facing opposition, while 2 Corinthians 6:14-17 emphasizes not being unequally yoked with unbelievers, urging believers to separate from unclean influences.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 23, 19, 42, 4, 4, 'went to their own company', 'Connection of Community and Worship', 'This connection highlights the theme of gathering with others in faith. Both passages emphasize the importance of being with a multitude in worship and sharing experiences within a community.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 23, 19, 119, 63, 63, 'their own company', 'Connection of Companionship', 'This connection highlights the theme of companionship among believers. Both passages emphasize the importance of being with those who fear God and keep His precepts.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 23, 44, 12, 11, 12, 'their own company', 'Prayer and Deliverance Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of communal prayer and divine intervention. In both passages, the believers gather together, first to report and later to pray, demonstrating their reliance on God for deliverance.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 23, 20, 13, 20, 20, 'their own company', 'Wisdom in Companionship', 'This connection highlights the importance of choosing companions wisely. In Acts, the apostles return to their own company, emphasizing the value of fellowship with those who share their faith, paralleling Proverbs'' warning about the consequences of associating with fools.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 23, 39, 3, 16, 16, 'their own company', 'Community of Believers', 'This connection highlights the theme of believers gathering and communicating with one another. Both passages emphasize the importance of speaking and sharing experiences among those who fear the Lord.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 23, 44, 1, 13, 14, 'their own company', 'Unity in Prayer and Support', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of community and support among the apostles. In Acts 4:23, they return to their own company after facing opposition, while Acts 1:13-14 describes their unity in prayer and supplication.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 24, 2, 20, 11, 11, NULL, 'Creation and Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize God''s role as the creator of heaven, earth, and the sea. This connection highlights the acknowledgment of God''s sovereignty in creation.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 24, 24, 32, 17, 17, 'made heaven, and earth', 'Creation and Divine Power', 'Both passages emphasize God''s role as the creator of heaven and earth, highlighting His great power. This connection underscores the belief in God''s sovereignty over all creation.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 24, 16, 9, 6, 6, NULL, 'Creation and Divine Sovereignty', 'Both passages emphasize God''s role as the creator of heaven, earth, and the sea. They highlight His sovereignty over all creation and the worship that is due to Him.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 24, 12, 19, 15, 15, 'thou art God, which hast made heaven, and earth', 'Creation Acknowledgment in Prayer', 'Both passages emphasize God''s role as the creator of heaven and earth. They highlight the acknowledgment of God''s sovereignty over all creation in prayer.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 24, 24, 10, 10, 12, 'which hast made heaven, and earth, and the sea, and all that in them is', 'God as Creator', 'Both passages emphasize God as the creator of heaven and earth. Acts 4:24 acknowledges God as the maker of all, while Jeremiah 10:12 states that He made the earth by His power.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 24, 19, 146, 5, 6, NULL, 'Creation and Divine Sovereignty', 'Both passages emphasize God''s role as the creator of heaven, earth, and the sea. This connection highlights the shared theme of divine sovereignty and support for believers.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 24, 52, 5, 16, 18, 'lifted up their voice to God', 'Unity in Prayer and Praise', 'This connection highlights the theme of communal prayer and gratitude to God. Both passages emphasize the importance of lifting one''s voice to God and giving thanks in all circumstances.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 25, 19, 2, 1, 6, 'Why did the heathen rage, and the people imagine vain things?', 'Connection of Rage and Vain Imagining', 'This connection highlights the shared theme of the heathen''s rage and the vain imaginations of people in both passages. The SOURCE verse quotes the TARGET passage directly, emphasizing the rebellion against God and His anointed.', 'quotation', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 25, 44, 1, 16, 16, 'by the mouth of thy servant David', 'Connection of David''s Prophecy', 'This connection highlights the use of David''s words in both passages. Acts 4:25 references David''s prophecy about the nations'' rage, while Acts 1:16 cites David''s words concerning Judas, linking the themes of betrayal and opposition.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 25, 44, 2, 30, 30, 'the heathen rage', 'Connection Between David and Christ', 'This connection highlights the role of David as a prophet, linking his words about the nations'' rage to the promise of Christ''s kingship. Both passages emphasize God''s plan through David''s lineage, culminating in Christ''s reign.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 26, 19, 2, 2, 2, 'against the Lord, and against his Christ', 'Connection of Rulers Against God', 'Both passages emphasize the opposition of earthly rulers against the Lord and His anointed. The phrases ''kings of the earth'' and ''rulers'' in both verses highlight this common theme of rebellion.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 26, 66, 17, 12, 14, 'the rulers were gathered together against the Lord', 'Kings Against the Lamb', 'Both passages emphasize the opposition of earthly rulers against divine authority. Acts 4:26 mentions rulers gathered against the Lord and His Christ, while Revelation 17:14 describes kings making war with the Lamb, who ultimately overcomes them.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 26, 27, 9, 24, 24, 'the rulers were gathered together', 'Connection of Kings and Rulers', 'Both passages emphasize the opposition of earthly rulers against God''s purposes. Acts 4:26 reflects the fulfillment of the conflict foretold in Daniel 9:24, where the transgressions are addressed through divine intervention.', 'theme', 0.363, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 26, 19, 83, 2, 8, 'gathered together against the Lord', 'Enemies Against God and His People', 'Both passages emphasize the opposition faced by God''s chosen ones. Acts 4:26 reflects the gathering of rulers against the Lord and His Christ, while Psalms 83:2-8 describes enemies conspiring against God''s people, Israel. This connection highlights the theme of collective hostility towards God''s authority.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 26, 44, 10, 38, 38, 'against the Lord, and against his Christ', 'Opposition to Jesus'' Mission', 'This connection highlights the opposition faced by Jesus, as indicated in Acts 4:26 with rulers standing against the Lord and His Christ. Acts 10:38 emphasizes Jesus'' mission of doing good and healing, which was met with resistance from those opposed to Him.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 26, 58, 1, 9, 9, 'rulers were gathered together against the Lord', 'Connection of Rulers and Anointing', 'Both passages emphasize the opposition of rulers against the Lord''s anointed. Acts 4:26 mentions rulers gathered against ''his Christ,'' while Hebrews 1:9 speaks of God anointing the one who loves righteousness, highlighting the significance of divine anointing amid opposition.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 26, 29, 3, 9, 14, 'the rulers were gathered together against the Lord', 'Conflict Against the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of rulers and nations against the Lord. Acts 4:26 mentions kings and rulers standing against Christ, while Joel 3:9-14 calls for the nations to assemble for judgment, indicating a confrontation with divine authority.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 27, 40, 27, 2, 2, 'Pontius Pilate', 'Connection between Jesus and Pilate', 'Both passages emphasize the involvement of Pontius Pilate in the events surrounding Jesus'' trial. Acts 4:27 mentions Pilate''s role in the conspiracy against Jesus, while Matthew 27:2 describes his action of delivering Jesus for trial.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 27, 44, 4, 30, 30, 'thy holy child Jesus', 'Connection of Jesus as Holy Child', 'Both passages emphasize ''thy holy child Jesus,'' linking His identity to the acts of healing and signs performed in His name. This connection highlights the significance of Jesus as the anointed one in the context of divine action.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 27, 42, 9, 22, 22, 'whom thou hast anointed', 'Connection of Suffering and Rejection', 'Both passages emphasize the suffering and rejection of Jesus. Acts 4:27 mentions the gathering against Jesus, while Luke 9:22 details the rejection He will face from leaders.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 27, 18, 14, 4, 4, 'thy holy child Jesus', 'Connection of Purity and Impurity', 'This connection highlights the theme of purity and the struggle against uncleanliness. Acts 4:27 mentions Jesus, the anointed one, facing opposition from unclean forces, while Job 14:4 questions the possibility of bringing forth purity from impurity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 27, 18, 15, 14, 14, 'thy holy child Jesus', 'Human Righteousness and Divine Action', 'This connection highlights the contrast between human unrighteousness and the divine nature of Jesus as the ''holy child.'' Both passages emphasize the limitations of humanity in achieving righteousness, suggesting a need for divine intervention.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 27, 19, 2, 2, 2, 'whom thou hast anointed', 'Connection of Anointed Figures', 'Both passages emphasize the opposition faced by God''s anointed. Acts 4:27 references Jesus as ''thy holy child'' while Psalms 2:2 speaks of ''his anointed,'' highlighting a shared theme of rulers conspiring against God''s chosen.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 27, 19, 45, 7, 7, 'whom thou hast anointed', 'Anointing of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the anointing of Jesus, highlighting His divine selection and role. Acts 4:27 refers to Jesus as ''thy holy child'' who is anointed, while Psalms 45:7 speaks of being anointed with ''the oil of gladness.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 28, 44, 2, 23, 23, 'determined before', 'Divine Determination in Events', 'Both passages emphasize God''s predetermined plan in the events surrounding Jesus'' crucifixion. The phrase ''determined before'' in Acts 4:28 parallels the ''determinate counsel'' in Acts 2:23, highlighting the divine orchestration of these events.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 28, 1, 50, 20, 20, 'thy hand and thy counsel determined', 'Divine Purpose in Adversity', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s sovereignty in human actions. Both passages emphasize that what may seem evil or harmful can ultimately fulfill God''s good purpose.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 28, 23, 46, 10, 10, 'thy counsel determined before to be done', 'Divine Counsel and Determination', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s sovereign counsel and determination in both passages. Acts 4:28 speaks of God''s hand and counsel determining events, while Isaiah 46:10 emphasizes that His counsel shall stand and He will accomplish His will.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 28, 40, 26, 24, 24, 'thy counsel determined before to be done', 'Divine Determination in Betrayal', 'Both passages emphasize the predetermined nature of events. Acts 4:28 speaks of God''s counsel determining actions, while Matthew 26:24 refers to the betrayal of the Son of Man as being written, indicating a divine plan.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 28, 23, 53, 10, 10, 'thy hand and thy counsel determined', 'Divine Determination of Suffering', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s predetermined plan in both passages. Acts 4:28 speaks of God''s hand and counsel determining events, while Isaiah 53:10 indicates that it pleased the Lord to bruise him, suggesting a divine purpose in suffering.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 28, 42, 24, 44, 46, 'thy hand and thy counsel determined', 'Fulfillment of Divine Plan', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of events predetermined by God. Acts 4:28 speaks of God''s counsel, while Luke 24:44-46 highlights the fulfillment of scripture concerning Christ''s suffering and resurrection.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 28, 44, 3, 18, 18, 'thy counsel determined before to be done', 'Connection of Divine Determination', 'Both passages emphasize God''s predetermined plan regarding Christ''s suffering. Acts 4:28 speaks of God''s counsel, while Acts 3:18 refers to God''s prior revelation through prophets.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 29, 44, 4, 13, 13, 'that with all boldness they may speak', 'Connection of Boldness in Acts', 'Both passages emphasize the boldness of Peter and John in speaking God''s word. The request for boldness in Acts 4:29 is exemplified in the actions of Peter and John in Acts 4:13.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 29, 44, 14, 3, 3, 'with all boldness they may speak thy word', 'Boldness in Speaking God''s Word', 'This connection highlights the theme of boldness in proclaiming God''s message. Both passages emphasize the empowerment of the servants to speak boldly, with Acts 4:29 requesting boldness and Acts 14:3 describing their boldness in action.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 29, 50, 1, 14, 14, 'boldness they may speak thy word', 'Boldness in Speaking the Word', 'This connection highlights the theme of boldness in proclaiming God''s word. Both passages emphasize the encouragement to speak with confidence despite challenges or threats.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 29, 55, 4, 17, 17, 'with all boldness they may speak thy word', 'Boldness in Preaching', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine support in preaching. Both passages emphasize the need for strength and boldness in proclaiming God''s word amidst challenges.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 29, 49, 6, 18, 20, 'that with all boldness they may speak', 'Boldness in Speaking the Gospel', 'This connection highlights the theme of boldness in proclaiming God''s word. Both passages emphasize the need for courage in speaking about the gospel amidst challenges.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 29, 55, 1, 7, 8, 'that with all boldness they may speak', 'Boldness in Speaking God''s Word', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of boldness in proclaiming the gospel despite fear and opposition. Acts 4:29 requests boldness to speak God''s word, while 2 Timothy 1:7-8 encourages believers to embrace their testimony without shame.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 29, 26, 2, 6, 6, 'with all boldness they may speak', 'Fearlessness in Proclamation', 'Both passages emphasize the need for boldness and fearlessness in the face of opposition. Acts 4:29 requests boldness to speak God''s word, while Ezekiel 2:6 encourages not to be afraid of rebellious adversaries.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 30, 44, 3, 6, 6, 'by the name of thy holy child Jesus', 'Healing in Jesus'' Name', 'Both passages emphasize the power of healing through the name of Jesus. Acts 3:6 demonstrates this power in action, while Acts 4:30 calls for signs and wonders to be done by the name of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 30, 44, 4, 27, 27, 'thy holy child Jesus', 'Connection of Jesus as Holy Child', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of Jesus as ''thy holy child.'' The first passage calls for healing and signs in His name, while the second acknowledges the opposition He faced from various leaders and groups.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 30, 2, 6, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Healing and Redemption', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine intervention through a ''stretched out'' action. Both passages emphasize God''s power to heal and redeem His people, linking physical healing in Acts to spiritual redemption in Exodus.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 30, 5, 4, 34, 34, 'signs and wonders', 'Connection of Signs and Wonders', 'Both passages emphasize the role of signs and wonders as manifestations of God''s power. Acts 4:30 refers to healing and wonders done in Jesus'' name, while Deuteronomy 4:34 recounts God''s signs and wonders in Egypt, showcasing His might.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 30, 24, 15, 15, 15, 'that signs and wonders may be done', 'Healing and Suffering', 'This connection highlights the theme of suffering and the desire for divine intervention. Both passages express a plea for God''s action in the face of persecution and affliction, with Acts referencing healing and Jeremiah seeking vindication.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 30, 24, 20, 11, 12, NULL, 'Divine Support in Persecution', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of divine support in times of distress. Acts 4:30 speaks of healing and signs done in Jesus'' name, while Jeremiah 20:11 highlights the Lord''s might against persecutors.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 30, 42, 9, 54, 56, NULL, 'Healing and Compassion Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of healing and compassion over destruction. Acts 4:30 speaks of healing through Jesus, while Luke 9:54-56 shows Jesus rebuking the desire for destruction, highlighting his mission to save lives.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 31, 40, 21, 22, 22, NULL, 'Connection Between Prayer and Boldness', 'Both passages emphasize the power of prayer. Acts 4:31 illustrates the results of prayer, leading to boldness, while Matthew 21:22 assures that believing prayer yields results.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 31, 23, 65, 24, 24, 'they had prayed', 'Prayer and Divine Response', 'Both passages emphasize the power of prayer and God''s immediate response. Acts 4:31 illustrates the believers'' boldness after prayer, while Isaiah 65:24 assures that God hears even before they call.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 31, 44, 2, 2, 2, 'filled with the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of Divine Presence', 'Both passages emphasize a powerful manifestation of the Holy Spirit. In Acts 2:2, the sound of a rushing wind signifies the arrival of the Holy Spirit, while Acts 4:31 describes the filling of the Holy Ghost and the resulting boldness in speaking.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 31, 44, 16, 25, 26, 'the place was shaken', 'Connection of Earthquakes and Prayer', 'Both passages emphasize the occurrence of an earthquake following prayer. In Acts 4:31, the place was shaken after prayer, while in Acts 16:26, an earthquake occurs as Paul and Silas pray and sing praises.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 31, 59, 1, 5, 5, NULL, 'Connection of Prayer and Wisdom', 'This connection highlights the act of asking God for guidance. Both passages emphasize the importance of seeking divine assistance, whether for boldness in speaking or for wisdom.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 31, 43, 14, 12, 12, 'spake the word of God with boldness', 'Connection of Boldness and Works', 'Both passages emphasize the empowerment of believers through the Holy Spirit. Acts 4:31 describes the boldness given to the apostles, while John 14:12 speaks of believers doing greater works, suggesting a divine enablement for ministry.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 31, 43, 15, 7, 7, 'spake the word of God with boldness', 'Connection of Prayer and Boldness', 'Both passages emphasize the power of prayer and its results. In Acts, the believers are filled with the Holy Ghost after prayer, enabling them to speak boldly, while in John, abiding in Christ leads to effective prayer.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 32, 46, 1, 10, 10, 'one heart and of one soul', 'Unity in Belief and Purpose', 'This connection highlights the theme of unity among believers. Both passages emphasize being of ''one heart and of one soul'' and ''one mind,'' indicating a call for harmony and shared purpose within the Christian community.', 'theme', 0.608, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 32, 49, 4, 2, 6, 'one heart and of one soul', 'Unity and Community in Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of unity among believers. Acts 4:32 speaks of being ''of one heart and of one soul,'' while Ephesians 4:2-6 encourages maintaining ''the unity of the Spirit.''', 'theme', 0.552, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 32, 60, 3, 8, 8, 'one heart and of one soul', 'Unity and Compassion in Community', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being of one mind and heart within a community. Acts 4:32 highlights the sharing of possessions, while 1 Peter 3:8 calls for compassion and love among brethren.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
