(44, 4, 32, 50, 2, 1, 2, 'one heart and of one soul', 'Unity in Belief and Purpose', 'Both passages emphasize being of one heart and one mind, highlighting the importance of unity among believers. Acts 4:32 describes a community sharing all things in common, while Philippians 2:1-2 calls for likemindedness and being of one accord.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 32, 47, 13, 11, 11, 'of one heart and of one soul', 'Unity in Belief and Mind', 'This connection highlights the theme of unity among believers. Both passages emphasize being ''of one mind'' and sharing all things in common, reflecting a communal spirit.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 32, 46, 12, 12, 14, 'one heart and of one soul', 'Unity in Community', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of unity among believers. Acts 4:32 describes the believers as being ''of one heart and of one soul,'' while 1 Corinthians 12:12-14 illustrates the unity of the body of Christ, highlighting that many members function as one.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 33, 43, 1, 16, 16, 'great grace was upon them all', 'Connection of Grace in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of grace. Acts 4:33 speaks of ''great grace'' upon the apostles, while John 1:16 refers to ''grace for grace,'' suggesting a continuous flow of grace from Jesus.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 33, 44, 1, 22, 22, 'witness of the resurrection', 'Witness of the Resurrection', 'This connection highlights the role of the apostles as witnesses of the resurrection of Jesus. Acts 1:22 establishes the requirement for apostles to witness the resurrection, while Acts 4:33 emphasizes their powerful testimony regarding it.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 33, 44, 1, 8, 8, 'great power gave the apostles witness', 'Connection of Apostolic Power', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of receiving power to be witnesses. Acts 1:8 speaks of receiving power from the Holy Ghost, while Acts 4:33 describes the apostles witnessing with great power.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 33, 41, 16, 20, 20, 'witness of the resurrection of the Lord Jesus', 'Connection of Apostolic Witness', 'Both passages emphasize the apostles'' role in preaching and witnessing the resurrection of Jesus. Acts highlights their powerful witness, while Mark describes the Lord working with them to confirm their message.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 4, 33, 42, 2, 52, 52, 'great grace was upon them all', 'Growth in Favor and Power', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of increasing favor, with Jesus growing in ''favour with God and man'' and the apostles experiencing ''great grace'' as they witness the resurrection. This connection highlights the theme of divine approval and empowerment in their respective contexts.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
